    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, other clauses like \"entire agreement\" provisions can trap you into forgetting previous conversations, while \"force majeure\" sections might be written so broadly they cover your own business risks. Watch out for \"survival\" clauses that keep your obligations alive long after the project ends, or \"changing terms\" language that lets the client modify rates or scope unilaterally without cause. These parts often hide significant shifts in power or obligation that feel unfair until you review the full context carefully.",
